  "prompt": "What are the requirements to attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting?",
  "response": "To attend the Berkshire Hathaway Annual Shareholder Meeting, you generally need to meet the following requirements:\n\n1. **Shareholder Status**: You must be a registered shareholder of Berkshire Hathaway. This usually means you need to own at least one share of the company's stock.\n\n2. **Admission Ticket**: Shareholders typically receive a ticket for admission, which is often sent out via mail or available through the company's investor relations website. It's important to keep this ticket as it is necessary for entry into the meeting.\n\n3. **Identification**: You may be asked to provide proof of identity, especially if you are registering or collecting your ticket on the day of the meeting.\n\n4. **Proxy Voting**: If you are a shareholder but cannot attend in person, you may have the option to vote by proxy. You would need to follow the instructions provided with your proxy materials.\n\n5. **Registration**: Some years, there may be a registration process for shareholders who plan to attend. This could be completed online or on-site, depending on the year.\n\n6. **COVID-19 Protocols**: Depending on the situation at the time of the meeting, there may be health and safety protocols in place, such as mask-wearing or social distancing requirements.\n\nIt's always best to check the official Berkshire Hathaway website or their investor relations page for the most up-to-date information regarding attendance, especially as requirements can change from year to year or due to special circumstances.",
